      <body>
         <pb n="1" facs="1869_02_25_Kniffler_Yokohama_von_H_C_Bock_Hamburg_1.tif"/>
         <p>Hamburg 25th February 1869<lb/>Messrs. L. Kniffler &amp; Co.<lb/>
            <lb/>I would first like to acknowledge receiving your <lb/>esteemed letter from 30th
                Dec. of last year <lb/>with the sales invoice for 3 boxes of <lb/>cloth, whose net
                proceeds of $ 1354.32 I have balanced <lb/>with £ 294.16.11 6/mth of/S. of the
                London Joint Stock Bank Ldon.<lb/>at a rate of 4/4¼Ce[?] with my kind regards and
                <lb/>subject to the usual provisos.<lb/>I duly noted the further contents of
                your<lb/>esteemed letter mentioned above and give <lb/>you my sincere thanks for
                your reports and information <lb/>about business there. <lb/>I confirm my respectful
                lines from 11th of this month<lb/> and following on from this I today have the
                <lb/>pleasure of supplying you with the enclosed invoice <lb/>for the remaining 50
                pcs. of black cloth, with the <lb/>request to credit me for them with the amount of
                <lb/>⟨Compte adant[?]⟩ B₻ 4,199.-. under the previous conditions <lb/>value date:
                16th February or to balance it on the <lb/>consignation account.<lb/>I refer in this
                regard wholly to your esteemed letter <lb/>from 28th January.<lb/>I am looking
                forward with pleasure to your future <lb/>messages and sign <lb/>⟨facturs⟩ Yours
                most cordially<lb/> H. C. Bock<lb/> (P.T.O.)</p>
         <pb facs="1869_02_25_Kniffler_Yokohama_von_H_C_Bock_Hamburg_2.tif" n="2"/>
         <p>P. S. May I also ask you to kindly credit me for <lb/>
            <hi rend="underline">B ₻ 16.8</hi> for haulage of a samples parcel with <lb/>
         </p>
         <figure>
            <figDesc>[Company sign Louis Kniffler &amp; Co. Letters with distinct serifs. Placed on a line drawn within the row are the letters L K &amp; C, below the line and underneath the row is the letter C]</figDesc>
         </figure>
         <p>#126/135 &amp; addressed and sent per overland mail and:<lb/>with many friendly
                greetings, Yours cordially <lb/>p Umst[?]</p>
         <pb facs="1869_02_25_Kniffler_Yokohama_von_H_C_Bock_Hamburg_3.tif" n="3"/>
         <pb facs="1869_02_25_Kniffler_Yokohama_von_H_C_Bock_Hamburg_4.tif" n="envelope"/>
         <p>
            <del rend="overstrike">P O S C</del>Steamer via Marseille<lb/>⟨3⟩ TT 41 HAMBURG I.
                A.<lb/>25 2<lb/>69<lb/>4-5N<lb/>Messrs. Kniffler+ Co.<lb/>⟨46⟩
                [...]<lb/>Yokohama<lb/>⟨1869<lb/>Hamburg 25th Feb.<lb/>H. C. Bock<lb/>rec[eived]
                20th April<lb/>Ans[wered] 30th Apr.<lb/>April<lb/>Kc Ro⟩</p>
      </body>
